{"parentUuid":"ec5a0c49-a6ce-4487-9d33-0c984a860c8d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqncQEbzWNjFLruJEXfQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01T34R8oA1b7ZcbjpLrNw93B","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\security-report.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14124,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14124,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqncPNWc4vqrARHoeLwq","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"c6993dca-59dc-437f-ab70-709e1a320cbf","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:38:43.043Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"c6993dca-59dc-437f-ab70-709e1a320cbf","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T34R8oA1b7ZcbjpLrNw93B","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstatus: clean\n3\tran_at: 2026-07-09T03:07:32Z\n4\tscope: diff\n5\tsince_commit: faabe9d6e59533dd144ce7895881dbe54fd7ddd2\n6\tcritical_count: 0\n7\twarning_count: 11\n8\tfixed_count: 1\n9\ttotal_findings: 12\n10\tsemgrep_findings: 7\n11\tosv_findings: 2\n12\tcheckov_findings: null\n13\ttrivy_findings: null\n14\t---\n15\t\n16\t# Security report — feature: metric-quotas (`PUT /v1/quotas` + per-customer enforcement)\n17\t\n18\t## Scope\n19\t\n20\tDiff against `HEAD` (`faabe9d`). Full change set: new `quotas` route/schema/service/repo,\n21\tAlembic `0003` (new `quotas` table + `api_keys.scope` column), the `POST /v1/events`\n22\tenforcement path, split-token/`scope` plumbing, `READ COMMITTED` engine pin, CORS `PUT`,\n23\t`AppError` envelope code, and the `--admin` seed flag. No `infra/` or `Dockerfile` in the\n24\tchange set → Checkov / Trivy / store-compliance not applicable this pass.\n25\t\n26\t**Remediation re-run delta (since the prior clean scan):** only test-harness + config-pin\n27\tchanges entered the diff —\n28\t`tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py` (worker-parity fix + AC20 regression guard),\n29\t`tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` (NEW adversarial RLS backstop test),\n30\t`tests/test_db_session_isolation.py` (NEW READ-COMMITTED pin regression test),\n31\t`src/db/session.py` (`isolation_level=\"READ COMMITTED\"` pin), and a human-revised **AC20**\n32\tin `.pipeline/acceptance.md` (perf criterion re-baselined to a relative ≤1.5× bound; not a\n33\tsecurity surface). All are risk-reducing or test-only; none introduces new attack surface.\n34\t\n35\t## Tools run this pass\n36\t\n37\t| Tool | Scope | Result |\n38\t|---|---|---|\n39\t| Semgrep (`auto`, `p/secrets`, `p/owasp-top-ten`, `p/python`) | full change set (36 files) | 7 findings — 2 real WARNINGs (CI mutable tags), 5 ERROR **false positives** in test DDL (triaged below) |\n40\t| OSV Scanner | project manifests (`poetry.lock`) | 2 ids (1 vuln, `pytest` — dev/test dep), max CVSS 6.8 < 7.0 floor |\n41\t| Gitleaks (`dir`) | full tree | 0 in the change set (all raw hits in `.venv/` + `.pipeline/`) |\n42\t| ASVS Tier-1 SAST (`asvs-sast.sh`) | change set | 0 critical, 0 warning |\n43\t| Lockfile / supply-chain (`lockfile-check.sh`) | change set | clean (exit 0) |\n44\t| Checkov / Trivy | — | n/a (no `infra/` or `Dockerfile` in the change set) |\n45\t\n46\t## Change vs. prior scan\n47\t\n48\t- Semgrep went 5 → 7 findings: the 2 prior `dangerous-subprocess-use-tainted-env-args`\n49\t  ERRORs in `test_perf_k6_load.py` (139/290) are **gone** — the worker-parity refactor\n50\t  restructured the uvicorn launch, which still uses safe list-form `subprocess.Popen(\n51\t  [sys.executable, \"-m\", \"uvicorn\", ...])` (no `shell=True`, only `str(port)`/`str(workers)`\n52\t  int-coerced tokens). Four new `avoid-sqlalchemy-text` ERRORs entered from the new RLS\n53\t  backstop test (all false positives — DDL over a uuid-generated role name; see triage).\n54\t- OSV unchanged (same 2 `pytest` ids, artifact byte-identical).\n55\t- No new critical, no new blocking finding. `status` stays **clean**.\n56\t\n57\t## Complete findings inventory\n58\t\n59\t| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n60\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n61\t| 1 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g | Medium (CVSS 6.8) | no | `poetry.lock` → `pytest@8.3.4` | action-required |\n62\t| 2 | osv | PYSEC-2026-1845 | Medium (CVSS 6.8) | no | `poetry.lock` → `pytest@8.3.4` | action-required |\n63\t| 3 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`quotas`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py:54` | fixed |\n64\t| 4 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`events`, `usage_rollup`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0001_*.py:66`, `0002_*.py:67` | reported-only |\n65\t| 5 | semgrep | github-actions-mutable-action-tag | Warning | no | `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml:54` | reported-only |\n66\t| 6 | semgrep | github-actions-mutable-action-tag | Warning | no | `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml:85` | reported-only |\n67\t| 7 | semgrep | avoid-sqlalchemy-text | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py:73` | reported-only |\n68\t| 8 | semgrep | avoid-sqlalchemy-text | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:44` | reported-only |\n69\t| 9 | semgrep | avoid-sqlalchemy-text | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:46` | reported-only |\n70\t| 10 | semgrep | avoid-sqlalchemy-text | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:47` | reported-only |\n71\t| 11 | semgrep | avoid-sqlalchemy-text | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:49` | reported-only |\n72\t| 12 | manual-6a | test-only ephemeral role password literal | Low | no | `tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:39` | reported-only |\n73\t\n74\t`total_findings = 12` (2 osv + 2 manual-6d + 7 semgrep + 1 manual-6a). Gitleaks (0 in-scope) +\n75\tASVS-SAST (0) + lockfile (0) contribute no rows. `critical_count = 0` after remediation;\n76\t`fixed_count = 1` (#3, carried in the working tree); `warning_count = 11` (all remaining rows\n77\tadvisory/non-blocking).\n78\t\n79\t## Semgrep triage (rows 5–11)\n80\t\n81\t- **#5 / #6 — `github-actions-mutable-action-tag` (WARNING, real).** Two CI steps in\n82\t  `pipeline-ci.yml` reference a mutable `@vN` tag rather than a pinned commit SHA — supply-chain\n83\t  hygiene. WARNING → advisory, non-blocking. Not auto-fixed (pinning third-party action SHAs is a\n84\t  CI-ownership decision). Recommend pinning to full-length commit SHAs.\n85\t- **#7 — `avoid-sqlalchemy-text` (ERROR, false positive).** `test_quota_migration.py:73` builds an\n86\t  f-string into `text()`, but the interpolated `columns`/`values` are static literals assembled\n87\t  in-function; every actual value is passed as a bound `:param`. No user-controlled interpolation.\n88\t  Test-harness only. Not exploitable.\n89\t- **#8–#11 — `avoid-sqlalchemy-text` (ERROR, false positive), new RLS backstop test.**\n90\t  `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:44,46,47,49` interpolate `role_name` into `CREATE ROLE` / `GRANT`\n91\t  DDL. `role_name` is `f\"rls_test_role_{uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]}\"` — internally generated, never\n92\t  user-controlled — and PostgreSQL does not accept bind parameters for identifiers (role names) in\n93\t  DDL, so an f-string is the only expressible form here. Runs solely against an ephemeral\n94\t  testcontainers Postgres, torn down after the test. No injection vector. Not exploitable → not a\n95\t  blocking critical. All bona-fide values in the test's data statements (`api_key_id`,\n96\t  `customer_id`) ARE passed as bound `:params` (lines 91, 98, 107, 148).\n97\t\n98\tThe five ERROR rows are recorded `exploitable: no` and excluded from `critical_count` (step-7\n99\texploitability judgment over raw scanner severity); `semgrep_findings` reports the raw count of 7,\n100\treconciled against the artifact.\n101\t\n102\t## Manual 6a triage (row 12)\n103\t\n104\t`role_password = \"test-role-password\"` (test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:39) is the password assigned to\n105\tthe throwaway `NOBYPASSRLS` role the test creates and `DROP`s within the same testcontainers\n106\tsession. It is not a production credential, appears in no runtime config/image/tfvars, and gitleaks\n107\tdoes not classify it as a secret (low entropy, obvious test literal). Reported for completeness;\n108\tnot a finding requiring remediation. No `.env` in the tracked change set; `git ls-files .env`\n109\treturns nothing; `.env` remains gitignored.\n110\t\n111\t## Fixes applied\n112\t\n113\t**#3 — `quotas` RLS tenant-isolation backstop made effective (`FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`)** in\n114\t`alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py` (applied in the prior remediation pass;\n115\tstill present in the working tree). The migration's app role owns the table and a table owner\n116\tbypasses non-`FORCE` RLS, so the backstop policy would be inert without `FORCE`. The added\n117\t`ALTER TABLE quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` closes that gap; safe for the app path because every\n118\t`quotas` access runs inside `scoped_transaction` (`SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id`). Confirmed\n119\tgone by this pass's consolidated re-scan.\n120\t\n121\t**This delta added a positive proof, not a fix:** the new `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` is an\n122\tadversarial test that connects as a real `NOBYPASSRLS` role (mirroring production `meterly_app`),\n123\tissues a filter-less query with the primary `api_key_id` predicate entirely removed, and asserts\n124\tthe RLS policy alone still confines the session to its own tenant's rows — and a second test proves\n125\tfail-closed behavior when `app.current_api_key_id` is unset. This turns the #3 FORCE fix from a\n126\tdeclared control into a tested one, and independently exercises the backstop that\n127\t`test_quotas_endpoint.py` could not (it runs as the testcontainers superuser, which bypasses RLS).\n128\t\n129\t## Could not remediate\n130\t\n131\tNone.\n132\t\n133\t## Action required (human decision — not auto-fixed)\n134\t\n135\t- **#1 / #2 — `pytest@8.3.4`** (GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g / PYSEC-2026-1845, CVSS ≈ 6.8 Medium).\n136\t  Dev/test-only tmpdir predictability, not on the request path. Below the deploy gate's CVSS ≥ 7.0\n137\t  floor → non-blocking. Safe upgrade: bump `pytest` to ≥ 8.3.5 in `pyproject.toml` + `poetry.lock`.\n138\t  Dependency bumps are the debugging agent's remit, not security's — reported only.\n139\t- **#4 — `events` and `usage_rollup` lack `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`** (pre-existing, migrations\n140\t  `0001`/`0002`, outside this diff). Same owner-bypass reasoning as #3. Recommend adding `FORCE` in a\n141\t  follow-up migration, or verifiably running migrations as a non-owner role. The explicit\n142\t  `api_key_id` predicate remains the effective primary control on those tables regardless.\n143\t\n144\t## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n145\t\n146\tAll 10 non-accepted-risk threats from `plan.md` §Threat Model have their named mechanism present;\n147\t2 accepted-risk rows (quota-data-at-rest, hot-row serialization latency) skipped per protocol. No\n148\tchange to the mechanism set this pass; the delta strengthens two efficacy answers:\n149\t\n150\t- **TOCTOU (Tampering):** the `isolation_level=\"READ COMMITTED\"` pin in `src/db/session.py:41` is now\n151\t  both documented (engine comment) and guarded by a deterministic regression test\n152\t  (`tests/test_db_session_isolation.py`), so the lock-then-read correctness the quota cap depends on\n153\t  cannot silently regress to REPEATABLE READ. Efficacy: ✓ (pin present + test-locked).\n154\t- **EoP data-level (IDOR/BOLA):** the RLS backstop is now proven effective by an adversarial\n155\t  NOBYPASSRLS test (`test_quotas_rls_backstop.py`), not merely declared. Efficacy: ✓ (primary\n156\t  `api_key_id` predicate present + backstop FORCE-enabled and independently exercised).\n157\t\n158\t`stride_mechanisms_verified = 10`, `stride_mechanisms_missing = 0`. Topology (Tier-2 throttle keyed\n159\ton `api_key_id`, not client IP), DB privilege (owner-bypass fixed on `quotas`; `events`/\n160\t`usage_rollup` flagged as #4), async runtime (no CPU-hard KDF on the loop in changed code), and\n161\tcontract drift (`customer_id` in the log redaction set) all re-confirmed unchanged.\n162\t\n163\t## STRIDE delta addendum (6f)\n164\t\n165\tThe delta introduces **no new attack surface** — new files are tests, and `src/db/session.py`\n166\tgained a configuration pin (isolation level), not a new entry point, outbound call, subprocess,\n167\tdeserializer, or data sink. `stride_new_threats = 0`; addendum empty. (The feature's own new\n168\tsurface — `PUT /v1/quotas`, `api_keys.scope`, the `quotas` table — was reconciled and covered in\n169\tthe prior pass and is unchanged here.)\n170\t\n171\t## ASVS 5.0.0 verification (6g)\n172\t\n173\tTriggered chapters: V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V12, V13, V14, V15, V16 (per plan `## ASVS Compliance`).\n174\t`n/a`: V3, V5, V7, V9, V10, V11, V17. L1+L2 verified universally; in-scope L3 = V15.4.x\n175\t(check-then-act atomicity) + V11.2.4 (constant-time compare, unchanged). The delta touches only\n176\tV15.4.x — the READ-COMMITTED pin + its regression test reinforce the check-then-increment\n177\tatomicity that V15.4.1/15.4.2 require; still met. All other chapter verdicts carry forward from the\n178\tprior pass. `l1_l2_missing = []`, `l3_in_scope_missing = []`, `doc_advisory = []`, `waivers = []`,\n179\t`reconciled = true`. No plan-cited ASVS mitigation left unimplemented.\n180\t\n181\t## Input-surface reconciliation\n182\t\n183\tUnchanged: 1 input source implemented (`PUT /v1/quotas`), 1 declared, both controls present\n184\t(validation contract + Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` rate limit). `uncontrolled = []`, reconciled.\n185\t\n186\t## Data-surface reconciliation\n187\t\n188\tUnchanged: `quotas.{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` + `api_keys.scope`, all classified\n189\tnon-sensitive operational config/authz metadata; at-rest control = RDS SSE. `sensitive = 0`,\n190\t`unprotected = []`, reconciled.\n191\t\n192\t## Migration scan (`0003`)\n193\t\n194\tUnchanged from prior pass: downgrade path present; `up` is expand-only; `down`'s `DROP TABLE` is the\n195\tdefined reversibility of a create-migration; no injectable SQL (all static DDL). Not a finding.\n196\t"}]},"uuid":"e0fa8cb9-3df5-4142-afa7-bf848787e6cb","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:38:43.063Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c6993dca-59dc-437f-ab70-709e1a320cbf","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
