{"parentUuid":"ec1c495a-4e76-4cf1-b7f3-8371e386a7a5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017sr5kaXZoknuueAnZK2s9p","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/api/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tHTTP API layer: FastAPI route handlers, request/response schemas (Pydantic v2), error envelope boundary, and edge-concern middleware (request ID, security headers, CORS, body-size guards).\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `routes/events.py` | `POST /v1/events` handler; calls `events_service.create_event`. |\n12\t| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n13\t| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n14\t| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n15\t| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. |\n16\t| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n17\t| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |\n18\t| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS (allows GET/POST/PUT). |\n19\t| `errors.py` | Error-envelope boundary: catches all unhandled exceptions and returns `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` with no stack/secret leakage. `AppError` lets a raised exception carry an explicit `app_code` (e.g. `quota_exceeded`) that overrides the default status->code map — needed because 429 is shared by two distinct codes (`rate_limited` vs `quota_exceeded`). |\n20\t\n21\t## Relationships\n22\t\n23\t**Public surface:**\n24\t- Imported by `src/main.py` to register routes with FastAPI.\n25\t- Exposes `get_app()` function which returns the fully-configured FastAPI instance.\n26\t\n27\t**Dependencies:**\n28\t- `middleware.py` and `errors.py` are registered once at app construction (middleware stack + exception handler).\n29\t- Each route handler uses `require_api_key` guard from `src/auth` to enforce authentication.\n30\t- Route handlers call `src/services.{events_service, usage_service}` to execute business logic.\n31\t- Schemas validate request bodies/parameters; malformed input raises Pydantic `ValidationError` → 422.\n32\t- Middleware and error boundary run for all routes, ensuring every response has proper headers and envelope shape.\n33\t\n34\t**Middleware ordering (in `main.py`):**\n35\t1. Request-ID / trace (outermost) — sets correlation context for all downstream logging.\n36\t2. Security headers — applied to every response.\n37\t3. CORS — explicit allowlist from config.\n38\t4. Body-size guard — reject Content-Length > 8 KiB.\n39\t5. Tier-1 edge throttle (pre-auth) — IP+route keyed.\n40\t6. `require_api_key` guard — auth.\n41\t7. Tier-2 per-key throttle (post-auth) — api_key_id keyed.\n42\t8. Route handler (innermost) — wrapped by error-envelope boundary.\n43\t\n44\t## Notes\n45\t\n46\t**Contract enforcement:**\n47\t- Request bodies are validated against Pydantic schemas; `extra='forbid'` rejects unknown fields.\n48\t- All string fields are bounded length (e.g., `customer_id` ≤128, `metric` ≤64).\n49\t- `quantity` is a decimal > 0 (no zero or negative); `idempotency_key` is alphanumeric + underscore/dash.\n50\t- GET `/v1/usage` requires a timezone-aware ISO-8601 `window` parameter within 90 days past to 1 hour future (naive datetimes rejected).\n51\t- PUT `/v1/quotas`: `limit_per_window` is an integer `>= 1` (`<= 1e15`, BIGINT-safe); `customer_id`/`metric` reuse the same anchored allowlists as events; unknown fields (including a client-supplied `api_key_id`/`scope`) are rejected outright.\n52\t\n53\t**Error handling:**\n54\t- Authentication failures (missing/invalid key) → 401/403 before handlers run.\n55\t- `PUT /v1/quotas` from a non-`admin`-scoped key → 403 `forbidden` (function-level authorization, checked in the route's composed dependency).\n56\t- Rate-limit exceeded (Tier-1 or Tier-2) → 429 `rate_limited` + Retry-After header.\n57\t- `POST /v1/events` over its quota → 429 `quota_exceeded` (distinct code, same status) + Retry-After to the next hour boundary; no event/rollup written (transaction rolled back).\n58\t- Schema validation failure → 422 with Pydantic error detail.\n59\t- Database errors (constraint violation, connection drop) → caught by error envelope → 500 (generic message, safe).\n60\t- Any unhandled exception → error envelope → 500, safe, no leak.\n61\t\n62\t**Security headers (all responses):**\n63\t- `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains` (production only; localhost omitted).\n64\t- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff` — disable MIME sniffing.\n65\t- `X-Frame-Options: DENY` — no embedding in iframes.\n66\t- `Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0` (API, not HTML).\n67\t"}]},"uuid":"e780aba0-10e0-4e11-a646-6bb8a276a6ac","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:18.185Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ec1c495a-4e76-4cf1-b7f3-8371e386a7a5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"e780aba0-10e0-4e11-a646-6bb8a276a6ac","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnewKS9YWVoVj5bDhR2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TVanNQRB9nswEET6cEWNv7","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\auth\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnevM9P5mXRNnpQzsRE","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"d76ea10a-c5cd-42f5-baa1-b5b4bc38e2b7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:18.363Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"d76ea10a-c5cd-42f5-baa1-b5b4bc38e2b7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TVanNQRB9nswEET6cEWNv7","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/auth/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tAuthentication and authorization layer: API key verification (split-token parsing and Argon2id credential check), in-process verification cache for performance, and Redis-backed rate limiting (Tier-1 pre-auth and Tier-2 post-auth, both fail-open).\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `__init__.py` | `require_api_key` FastAPI dependency guard: parses the `Authorization: Bearer` header, checks the verification cache, falls back to DB lookup + Argon2id verify on cache miss, sets the authenticated `api_key_id` in request state. |\n12\t| `api_key.py` | Split-token key parsing (`mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>`), verification logic (Argon2id check), cache TTL management, revocation status check. `AuthenticatedPrincipal.scope` (`\"ingest\"` default, `\"admin\"` elevated) rides the same cached principal. |\n13\t| `rate_limit.py` | Tier-1 (pre-auth, IP+route keyed) and Tier-2 (post-auth, api_key_id keyed) Redis token-bucket limiters; both fail open (log warning, allow request) on Redis connection error. |\n14\t\n15\t**Authorization scope (function-level, on top of authentication):**\n16\t- `AuthenticatedPrincipal.scope` is `\"ingest\"` by default; `\"admin\"` is a superset scope, not a separate key family — an admin-scoped key does everything an ingest key does, plus is permitted to call `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n17\t- Only `src/api/routes/quotas.py`'s composed dependency checks `scope` (`principal.scope == \"admin\"`, else `HTTPException(403)`); every other route ignores it, so existing behavior is unchanged.\n18\t- Provisioned via `scripts/seed_api_key.py --admin` (defaults to `\"ingest\"` without the flag); this is also the DAST-context admin test key (DAST-3).\n19\t\n20\t## Relationships\n21\t\n22\t**Public surface:**\n23\t- `require_api_key` is imported by `src/api.routes` as a FastAPI dependency (guard). When used, it populates `request.state.api_key_id` with the authenticated principal's ID.\n24\t- Tier-1 and Tier-2 rate limiters are called from `src/api.middleware` (Tier-1) and `src/api.routes.{events, usage}` (Tier-2).\n25\t\n26\t**Dependencies:**\n27\t- `api_key.py` imports `src.crypto` for Argon2id verify and `src.db.session_context` for credential lookup on cache miss.\n28\t- `api_key.py` imports `src.logging.get_logger` for debug/warning logs (e.g., revocation, cache miss).\n29\t- `rate_limit.py` imports `src.config.settings` for rate limits (per-key `rate_limit_per_sec`) and `src.redis_client` for token-bucket state.\n30\t- Both modules are async (return coroutines for use in async context).\n31\t\n32\t**Request flow:**\n33\t1. **Tier-1 throttle** (IP+route keyed) runs first in middleware, pre-auth. Checks Redis, fails open.\n34\t2. **`require_api_key`** parses and verifies the split token, caches verified keys.\n35\t3. **Tier-2 throttle** (api_key_id keyed) runs post-auth. Checks Redis with the now-authenticated principal's ID, fails open.\n36\t4. If any throttle rejects (rate limit exceeded), the handler never runs; 429 is returned.\n37\t\n38\t## Notes\n39\t\n40\t**Verification cache:**\n41\t- In-process TTL-bounded cache (default: 5 minutes) keyed on the public `key_id` (not the secret).\n42\t- On cache hit, constant-time comparison of the cached secret against the request secret (no Argon2id cost).\n43\t- On cache miss, DB lookup + Argon2id verify (expensive, ~100ms), then store in cache for future hits.\n44\t- Cache is per-process; horizontal scale-out (multiple Fargate tasks) means cache hit rates vary per task (not a correctness issue, just a performance variance).\n45\t\n46\t**Revocation:**\n47\t- API key lookup checks the `revoked_at` column; a non-null value means the key is revoked.\n48\t- Revoked keys are rejected with 403 and not cached.\n49\t- Cache invalidation is not real-time (revocations take up to 5 minutes to propagate across all tasks).\n50\t- Recorded in `.pipeline/plan.md` as an accepted risk (noted for future key-revocation SLA if tighter bounds are needed).\n51\t\n52\t**Rate limiting — fail-open behavior:**\n53\t- If Redis is unavailable, a Redis `ConnectionError` is caught and logged as a warning.\n54\t- The request is allowed through (traffic is not dropped).\n55\t- Recorded in `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` as an availability tradeoff: prefer dropping rate limits over dropping user requests.\n56\t\n57\t**Rate limiting — Tier-1 pre-auth:**\n58\t- Keyed on IP + route (e.g., `ratelimit:tier1:POST:/v1/events:192.0.2.1`).\n59\t- Limits apply per route (different budgets can be configured per route if needed).\n60\t- Protects against flooding *before* we pay an Argon2id cost.\n61\t- Runs in middleware; all routes inherit the same policy.\n62\t\n63\t**Rate limiting — Tier-2 post-auth:**\n64\t- Keyed on `api_key_id` (e.g., `ratelimit:tier2:123`).\n65\t- Limit is the key's `rate_limit_per_sec` column (default: 100 req/s).\n66\t- Per-customer isolation: two customers sharing one client IP each get independent buckets (discriminating test in `tests/integration/test_rate_limit.py`).\n67\t- Runs after auth in the route handler; only affects authenticated requests.\n68\t"}]},"uuid":"93b62b0e-8dce-41cb-b367-07fff569b2e9","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:18.384Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d76ea10a-c5cd-42f5-baa1-b5b4bc38e2b7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"93b62b0e-8dce-41cb-b367-07fff569b2e9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnewKS9YWVoVj5bDhR2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011wn3Y7LfjscVGpAZBzHYSv","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnevM9P5mXRNnpQzsRE","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"0086ee71-87cb-41e0-a0f3-0c6d1942e918","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:19.036Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"0086ee71-87cb-41e0-a0f3-0c6d1942e918","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011wn3Y7LfjscVGpAZBzHYSv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/repositories/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tData access layer: SQL queries with parameterization, row-level scoping (by authenticated `api_key_id`), and minimal-field projections. All database I/O is encapsulated here.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `events_repo.py` | `create_or_replay_event(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start)` — INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO NOTHING (idempotency). Also `upsert_rollup()` (called only on insert success). |\n12\t| `usage_repo.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start)` — SELECT from `usage_rollup` scoped by `api_key_id`. Returns None if missing (caller handles zero conversion). |\n13\t| `api_keys_repo.py` | `find_active_key_by_key_id(key_id)` — SELECT from `api_keys` by public `key_id` (used by auth cache miss); returns the full row including `scope`. `create_api_key(..., scope=\"ingest\")` — the only key-provisioning path. |\n14\t| `quotas_repo.py` | `upsert_quota(...)` — `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted`, reporting create-vs-replace in one round-trip. `read_tenant_quota_state_locked(...)` — the atomic check-then-decide: locks the quota row (`FOR UPDATE`), then reads the current-window rollup total as a **separate, fresh** statement (see *Notes* below for why). Returns `None` when no quota exists (unlimited, no lock taken). |\n15\t\n16\t## Relationships\n17\t\n18\t**Public surface:**\n19\t- Imported by `src/services.{events_service, usage_service, quota_service}` to execute queries.\n20\t- `api_keys_repo` is also imported by `src/auth.api_key` (credential lookup on cache miss).\n21\t- `quotas_repo` is imported by both `quota_service` (the upsert) and `events_service` (the read-and-decide).\n22\t\n23\t**Dependencies:**\n24\t- All functions are async; they receive an `AsyncSession` from the service layer (obtained via `src/db.session_context`).\n25\t- Queries use SQLAlchemy ORM with bound parameters (no string concatenation); all user input is parameterized.\n26\t- RLS is set per-transaction by `src/db.session_context` before the first query runs (sets the `app.current_api_key_id` PostgreSQL context variable).\n27\t\n28\t**Row-level security:**\n29\t- Every query includes the authenticated `api_key_id` in the WHERE clause (primary application-layer control).\n30\t- E.g., `WHERE api_key_id = :auth_key AND customer_id = :customer_id` — no unscoped queries.\n31\t- PostgreSQL RLS policy (`USING (api_key_id = current_setting(...))`) is the backstop; the app role has no `BYPASSRLS`.\n32\t- If a query accidentally omits the `api_key_id` filter, RLS blocks it at the database level (defense-in-depth).\n33\t\n34\t**Field projections (minimal surface):**\n35\t- `create_or_replay_event` returns only `{event_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, window_start, idempotent_replay}` — not the full row (which includes `created_at`, `event_time`, `api_key_id`).\n36\t- `read_usage` returns only `{customer_id, metric, window_start, total_quantity, event_count}` — not internal bookkeeping (`updated_at`, `api_key_id`).\n37\t- `api_keys_repo.get_by_key_id` returns the full row (needed by auth for `secret_hash`, `rate_limit_per_sec`, `revoked_at`).\n38\t\n39\t**Constraint enforcement:**\n40\t- `create_or_replay_event` relies on the `UNIQUE (api_key_id, idempotency_key)` constraint at the DB level to detect duplicates.\n41\t- If a duplicate key is encountered, PostgreSQL raises an `IntegrityError` (caught by service layer) → the service reads the original row instead.\n42\t- `quantity > 0` and other domain constraints are enforced by CHECK constraints in the schema (verified at insert time).\n43\t\n44\t## Notes\n45\t\n46\t**ON CONFLICT pattern:**\n47\t- The idempotency mechanism uses `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, idempotency_key) DO NOTHING RETURNING id, ...`.\n48\t- If the unique constraint is violated, the INSERT returns no rows.\n49\t- The service layer checks `if result` — if a row was returned, this request won the insert; if not, a duplicate is detected.\n50\t\n51\t**RLS context setup:**\n52\t- Before any query, `src/db.session_context` sets `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :id` in the transaction.\n53\t- This context variable is read by the PostgreSQL RLS policy on every table access.\n54\t- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction (automatically cleared at commit), so no context leakage across requests.\n55\t\n56\t**Quota lock-then-read pattern (why it's two statements, not one):**\n57\t- `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` deliberately issues the `FOR UPDATE` lock on `quotas` and the `usage_rollup` read as two separate statements, not a single `LEFT JOIN ... FOR UPDATE OF q` query.\n58\t- PostgreSQL's `FOR UPDATE` only forces a fresh re-check (`EvalPlanQual`) of the *locked* row itself when a blocked waiter unblocks after the holder commits — it does **not** force a fresh snapshot for another table read in the same statement, including a joined one.\n59\t- A single combined statement lets a waiter that queued before the holder committed read `usage_rollup` from its own stale pre-wait snapshot — verified empirically during implementation: every concurrent waiter read the same stale total and all got admitted, silently breaking the cap.\n60\t- Issuing the `usage_rollup` read as its own statement *after* the lock is acquired gives it a fresh READ COMMITTED snapshot that does include everything the previous holder just committed — this is what makes `current_total` accurate for every waiter, not just the first uncontended caller (`tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py`).\n61\t\n62\t**Async pattern:**\n63\t- All functions are async; they use `await session.execute(...)` for queries.\n64\t- They receive an `AsyncSession` that's already connected and in a transaction (setup by `src/db.session_context`).\n65\t- No explicit connection management in the repo; the session is provided by the caller.\n66\t"}]},"uuid":"4e5e9a79-d2fc-483a-89fa-485229e0d774","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:19.053Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0086ee71-87cb-41e0-a0f3-0c6d1942e918","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"4e5e9a79-d2fc-483a-89fa-485229e0d774","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnewKS9YWVoVj5bDhR2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017AbUrdKQ1zRJLi7AEDKtgb","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnevM9P5mXRNnpQzsRE","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"4b98a871-2ef3-4209-b722-e8f2e4ea6373","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:19.384Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"4b98a871-2ef3-4209-b722-e8f2e4ea6373","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017AbUrdKQ1zRJLi7AEDKtgb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/services/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tBusiness logic layer: event ingestion (with idempotency and counter atomicity), usage aggregation, and time-window calculations. Orchestrates repositories and enforces domain invariants.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `events_service.py` | `create_event(principal, payload)` — inserts an event, checks the caller's quota (if any) on the winning-insert branch, and increments the hourly counter, all in one transaction; idempotent on `idempotency_key`. Raises `QuotaExceededError` (429 `quota_exceeded`) when `R + Q > L`, which rolls back the event insert. Returns the created/replayed event. |\n12\t| `usage_service.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window)` — reads the aggregated counter for a time bucket; returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n13\t| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n14\t| `time_windows.py` | `window_start_utc(ts: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by all three services. |\n15\t\n16\t## Relationships\n17\t\n18\t**Public surface:**\n19\t- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage, quotas}` to execute the core business operations.\n20\t\n21\t**Dependencies:**\n22\t- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, quotas_repo}` to insert the event, check the quota, and upsert the counter.\n23\t- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n24\t- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n25\t- All three services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs.\n26\t- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.\n27\t\n28\t**Transaction boundary:**\n29\t- `create_event` wraps the event insert, the quota check, and the rollup upsert in one PostgreSQL transaction (via `src/db/session_context`).\n30\t- This atomicity ensures that if the insert wins (no existing `idempotency_key`) and the quota check passes, the counter increments exactly once.\n31\t- If the insert loses (duplicate key), the quota is never consulted and neither the counter nor any side effect happens — a no-op.\n32\t- If the quota check rejects (`R + Q > L`), raising `QuotaExceededError` propagates out of the transaction context and rolls it back — the event insert is undone and the counter is never touched (no partial write).\n33\t- `upsert_tenant_quota` wraps the quota upsert in its own transaction; a single `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0)` reports create-vs-replace with no second round-trip.\n34\t\n35\t## Notes\n36\t\n37\t**Idempotency guarantee:**\n38\t- The unique constraint `UNIQUE (api_key_id, idempotency_key)` on the `events` table is the source of truth.\n39\t- Exactly one of N concurrent identical requests will succeed; the rest get a duplicate-key constraint violation (caught, no exception raised to handler) and fall through to a replay branch.\n40\t- The replay branch reads the original event from the table and returns it, so the caller sees a consistent result across retries.\n41\t- Recorded in the plan as the **AC-CONCURRENCY** mechanism: 50 concurrent same-key POSTs produce exactly one row and 49 get the replay response (200 vs. 201).\n42\t\n43\t**Counter atomicity:**\n44\t- The event insert and the rollup upsert are in one transaction, so both commit or both roll back.\n45\t- This means a counter never gets incremented without the event being persisted (no partial writes).\n46\t- Also means a duplicate event never increments the counter (no double-counting).\n47\t- The counter uses `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` with `total_quantity + EXCLUDED.total_quantity` to handle the increment (PostgreSQL's row-level conflict resolution, atomic at the SQL level).\n48\t\n49\t**Time-window semantics:**\n50\t- A timestamp is floored to its hour (UTC) to get the `window_start`. E.g., `2026-07-06T14:35:42Z` → `2026-07-06T14:00:00Z`.\n51\t- The floor is done explicitly in Python (`ts.replace(minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)`) rather than in the database, because PostgreSQL's `date_trunc('hour', ts)` is STABLE (depends on session timezone), not IMMUTABLE, so it cannot be used in a stored generated column.\n52\t- All windows are in UTC; clients must provide timezone-aware ISO-8601 timestamps on GET.\n53\t\n54\t**Scoping by api_key_id:**\n55\t- Both services receive the authenticated `api_key_id` from the route guard (set in `request.state`).\n56\t- Both services pass it to the repository layer, which includes it in the WHERE clause (e.g., `WHERE api_key_id = :auth_key AND customer_id = :customer_id`).\n57\t- This is the primary RLS mechanism; the PostgreSQL RLS policy is the backstop.\n58\t"}]},"uuid":"13a2c886-d505-4863-9aa2-8d14121ea4c3","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:19.403Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4b98a871-2ef3-4209-b722-e8f2e4ea6373","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"13a2c886-d505-4863-9aa2-8d14121ea4c3","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnewKS9YWVoVj5bDhR2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011n91KVUSK7QC7xLrxJH2Dm","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\db\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnevM9P5mXRNnpQzsRE","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"98a7aa10-823c-49b9-a390-014cc1d225c7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:19.751Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"98a7aa10-823c-49b9-a390-014cc1d225c7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011n91KVUSK7QC7xLrxJH2Dm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/db/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tDatabase connectivity and session management: async SQLAlchemy session factory, connection pooling, transaction scope, and per-transaction RLS context setup.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `session.py` | `session_context(api_key_id)` — async context manager that opens a transactional AsyncSession, sets the RLS context variable, and yields the session. Used by services to run queries with both transaction and RLS guarantees. |\n12\t\n13\t## Relationships\n14\t\n15\t**Public surface:**\n16\t- `session_context` is imported by `src/services.{events_service, usage_service}` to create transactional scopes for queries.\n17\t\n18\t**Dependencies:**\n19\t- Imports `src.config.settings` for the `DATABASE_URL` (async connection string).\n20\t- Imports SQLAlchemy's async engine/session machinery.\n21\t\n22\t**RLS mechanism:**\n23\t- At the start of each transaction (entered via `async with session_context(api_key_id)`), the context manager executes `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :api_key_id`.\n24\t- This PostgreSQL session variable is read by the RLS policy on every table access within the transaction.\n25\t- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction, so the context is automatically cleared at commit (no cleanup needed).\n26\t- This ensures that even if a repository query accidentally omits the `api_key_id` filter, RLS blocks the access (defense-in-depth).\n27\t\n28\t## Notes\n29\t\n30\t**Connection pooling:**\n31\t- The async engine uses a connection pool (default: 5-20 connections).\n32\t- At startup (lifespan in `src/main.py`), the pool is created and warmed.\n33\t- At shutdown, all connections are drained and closed (graceful shutdown).\n34\t\n35\t**Transaction scope:**\n36\t- Every service call wraps its queries in a `session_context` block, ensuring all queries are in one transaction.\n37\t- For `create_event`, both the event insert and the rollup upsert happen in the same transaction (atomicity).\n38\t- For `read_usage`, the single SELECT is in its own transaction (isolation).\n39\t\n40\t**Async pattern:**\n41\t- The session is async; all I/O operations (execute, fetch, etc.) are awaited.\n42\t- The context manager is async (uses `async with`).\n43\t- Services must be async to use the context manager (all routes in `src/api` are async).\n44\t\n45\t**Database connection string:**\n46\t- Expected in the `DATABASE_URL` environment variable.\n47\t- Must be an async URL (e.g., `postgresql+asyncpg://...`).\n48\t- Credentials are fetched by `src/config.secrets.fetch_db_credentials()` from AWS Secrets Manager at startup (or from `DATABASE_URL` if that's set).\n49\t"}]},"uuid":"eaa06e2c-1fc7-4396-bf0d-462dc5d04807","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:19.766Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"98a7aa10-823c-49b9-a390-014cc1d225c7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"eaa06e2c-1fc7-4396-bf0d-462dc5d04807","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnewKS9YWVoVj5bDhR2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011KrU7vurT4oBHfCfn3n7Pa","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnevM9P5mXRNnpQzsRE","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"ccf9d6a4-931c-4bfe-b2a1-9cde59994259","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:20.481Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"ccf9d6a4-931c-4bfe-b2a1-9cde59994259","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011KrU7vurT4oBHfCfn3n7Pa","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tThe main application package for the Meterly metering engine. Contains the FastAPI application entry point, API route handlers, domain services, data repositories, and supporting infrastructure (auth, logging, observability, database, configuration).\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| Directory / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `main.py` | FastAPI application factory; middleware registration; lifespan startup/shutdown (DB pool, Redis, OTel/Sentry init). |\n12\t| `api/` | HTTP API layer: routes, schemas, error handlers, middleware (request ID, security headers, CORS). Public surface for all incoming HTTP requests. |\n13\t| `services/` | Business logic layer: event ingestion, usage aggregation, time-window calculations. Orchestrates repositories and enforces invariants (idempotency, counter atomicity). |\n14\t| `repositories/` | Data access layer: SQL queries wrapped with parameterization, RLS scoping, and minimal-field projections. All database I/O is here. |\n15\t| `auth/` | Authentication and authorization: API key verification (split-token, Argon2id verify cache), Tier-1 and Tier-2 rate limiting (Redis token buckets). |\n16\t| `logging/` | Structured logging facade (structlog): request middleware, PII redaction, observability correlation. |\n17\t| `observability/` | OTel and Sentry integration: trace/span management, release tagging, error scrubbing. |\n18\t| `config/` | Configuration and secrets management: environment variables, dependency injection, Secrets Manager fetch. |\n19\t| `db/` | Database connectivity: async SQLAlchemy session factory, RLS scoping, connection pooling. |\n20\t| `crypto/` | Cryptographic utilities: Argon2id hashing, constant-time comparison, credential generation. |\n21\t\n22\t## Relationships\n23\t\n24\t**Layered architecture:**\n25\t- **Request flow (inbound):** HTTP request → `main.py` (middleware stack) → `api/` routes → `auth/` guards (rate limit, API key verify) → request handler → `services/` business logic → `repositories/` SQL → database.\n26\t- **Response flow (outbound):** Database result → `repositories/` minimal projection → `services/` aggregate/format → `api/` routes → `api/errors.py` error envelope → HTTP response (via middleware: add correlation/security headers).\n27\t\n28\t**Public surfaces (facades):**\n29\t- `api.routes` — HTTP handlers; imported by `main.py` to register with FastAPI. Entry point for all external callers.\n30\t- `auth` — `require_api_key` guard; imported by routes to gate handler execution. Enforces two rate-limit tiers.\n31\t- `logging.get_logger` — centralized structured logging facade with PII redaction. Imported by every module that logs.\n32\t- `config.settings` — environment configuration singleton; imported at startup and by modules needing env values.\n33\t- `db.session_context` — async session factory for transactional scope. Imported by services and repositories.\n34\t\n35\t**Dependencies (inbound imports):**\n36\t- `repositories` are imported only by `services` (single-responsibility: services orchestrate the data layer).\n37\t- `services` are imported only by `api.routes` (single-responsibility: routes dispatch to business logic).\n38\t- `auth` is imported by `main.py` (to register guards) and by `api.routes` (to call the guard).\n39\t- `logging`, `config`, `db` are imported by multiple modules as cross-cutting infrastructure.\n40\t\n41\t## Notes\n42\t\n43\t**Environment variables** consumed by `config/settings.py`:\n44\t- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL connection string (async, with app-role credentials).\n45\t- `REDIS_URL` — ElastiCache Redis URL for rate limiting.\n46\t- `SENTRY_DSN` — Sentry error-tracking endpoint (omit to disable; non-gating).\n47\t- `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` — OTel collector endpoint (ADOT sidecar in prod; omit to disable).\n48\t- `LOG_LEVEL` — structlog verbosity (default: INFO).\n49\t- `RELEASE_SHA` — commit SHA (set by the container build; used for Sentry/X-Ray tagging).\n50\t\n51\t**Deployment contract:**\n52\t- The container entrypoint runs `uvicorn src.main:app` (see `Dockerfile`).\n53\t- At startup (`lifespan`), all async resources are initialized (DB, Redis, OTel, Sentry).\n54\t- At shutdown (SIGTERM), resources drain gracefully (connection close, request drain, cleanup).\n55\t- `/health` (liveness) requires no dependencies and can be called at any time.\n56\t- `/health/ready` (readiness) requires the DB and migration head to be intact.\n57\t"}]},"uuid":"c053395b-7499-4996-a411-eddbee30ca40","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:20.514Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ccf9d6a4-931c-4bfe-b2a1-9cde59994259","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"c053395b-7499-4996-a411-eddbee30ca40","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnewKS9YWVoVj5bDhR2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UYPKysoKuwURTMdmDbfxBL","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\scripts\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnevM9P5mXRNnpQzsRE","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"b9d759c9-b6a1-41b7-8428-505975f570c9","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:20.860Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"b9d759c9-b6a1-41b7-8428-505975f570c9","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UYPKysoKuwURTMdmDbfxBL","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# scripts/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tUtility scripts for deployment, testing, and operational tasks: API key seeding, smoke checks, security scanning hooks, and CI workflow helpers.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `seed_api_key.py` | Generates and provisions a new API key: creates a random secret, hashes it with Argon2id, inserts it into the database as a new `api_keys` row. Output includes the public key_id and the secret (displayed once, never stored). Used for initial key setup and test key generation. |\n12\t| `smoke_import_check.py` | Python import smoke test: attempts to import the main app module (`src.main`) to catch syntax errors and early import failures before deployment. Run by the CI smoke-check hook. |\n13\t| `ci/lockfile-check.sh` | Validates that `poetry.lock` is in sync with `pyproject.toml` (no stale/diverged dependencies). Run by CI before build. |\n14\t| `ci/asvs-sast.sh` | ASVS Tier-1 SAST hook: runs Semgrep with project-specific rules to detect common security issues. Output feeds into the security report. |\n15\t| `ci/dast-review.sh` | DAST review aggregator: collects and summarizes findings from runtime security scanning (e.g., OWASP ZAP). Run post-deployment. |\n16\t| `ci/guard-source-markers.sh` | Validates that all deployment-critical markers are in place (e.g., PR description file, release notes). |\n17\t| `ci/store-compliance.sh` | Validates app store (Apple, Google Play) compliance metadata (not applicable for this API-only project; stub for cross-repo standardization). |\n18\t\n19\t## Relationships\n20\t\n21\t**Invocation:**\n22\t- `seed_api_key.py` — run manually during setup: `poetry run python scripts/seed_api_key.py`.\n23\t- `smoke_import_check.py` — run by CI smoke check: `poetry run python scripts/smoke_import_check.py`.\n24\t- `ci/*.sh` scripts — run by GitHub Actions workflows (pipeline-ci.yml, deploy.yml, etc.).\n25\t\n26\t**Entrypoints for external systems:**\n27\t- CI/CD pipelines call the `ci/*.sh` scripts to validate and report on the change.\n28\t- Human operators call `seed_api_key.py` to provision new API keys (for staging/test/prod as needed).\n29\t\n30\t## Notes\n31\t\n32\t**API key provisioning:**\n33\t- `seed_api_key.py` reads the database connection from `DATABASE_URL` env var (or Secrets Manager if not set).\n34\t- Takes optional CLI args: `--key_id` (public key handle, defaults to generated random), `--label` (human description), `--rate_limit_per_sec` (token bucket limit, defaults to 100).\n35\t- Outputs: the full token `mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>`, which should be shared with the caller.\n36\t- The script runs in the context of the deployed environment (same database as the app).\n37\t\n38\t**Smoke check:**\n39\t- `smoke_import_check.py` is fast (< 1 second) and safe (no state changes, no external calls).\n40\t- Used as a pre-flight check before running the full test suite (catches early failures).\n41\t\n42\t**CI integration:**\n43\t- All `ci/*.sh` scripts are invoked by GitHub Actions workflows.\n44\t- They read artifacts and env vars set by prior steps (e.g., test results, security scan outputs).\n45\t- They exit with status code 0 (pass) or non-zero (fail), which GitHub Actions interprets as workflow pass/fail.\n46\t\n47\t**Security scanning hooks:**\n48\t- `asvs-sast.sh` runs Semgrep (via Docker) on the changed code.\n49\t- Output is JSON, aggregated into the security report.\n50\t- Flags like `--docker` enable Docker-based execution (for Semgrep to work on systems without native Python/Node/Go runtimes).\n51\t"}]},"uuid":"653c54a2-ea2a-4159-a5f5-c1e93350bab6","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:20.879Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b9d759c9-b6a1-41b7-8428-505975f570c9","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"653c54a2-ea2a-4159-a5f5-c1e93350bab6","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnewKS9YWVoVj5bDhR2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LYLnyjZNMHaSuT6yx6QgSD","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\alembic\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"output_tokens":721,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":721,"cache_read_input_tokens":29051,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6026,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6026,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnevM9P5mXRNnpQzsRE","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"23171d46-d443-4791-bd62-685237bd998f","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:21.080Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"23171d46-d443-4791-bd62-685237bd998f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LYLnyjZNMHaSuT6yx6QgSD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# alembic/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tDatabase schema migrations using Alembic (SQLAlchemy's migration tool): version-controlled schema changes, automated upgrade/downgrade paths, and multi-environment deployment hooks.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `versions/0001_create_api_keys_and_events.py` | Migration: create `api_keys` and `events` tables with constraints, indexes, and RLS policies (initial schema creation). Down path: drop both tables in FK-safe order. |\n12\t| `versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` | Migration: create `usage_rollup` table and backfill aggregates from existing `events` rows (expand + backfill pattern). Down path: drop the table and restore original `events` data if needed. |\n13\t| `env.py` | Alembic runtime configuration: detects whether to run in \"offline\" (SQL script generation) or \"online\" (live DB) mode; configures the SQLAlchemy engine and metadata. |\n14\t| `script.py.mako` | Template for auto-generated migration files (not typically modified). |\n15\t\n16\t## Relationships\n17\t\n18\t**Public surface:**\n19\t- Run at deployment time: `alembic upgrade head` (applies all pending migrations).\n20\t- Run locally after pulling schema changes: `alembic upgrade head`.\n21\t- Migrations are immutable once committed (Alembic enforces this via the version table).\n22\t\n23\t**Dependencies:**\n24\t- Migrations reference the SQLAlchemy models (not directly, but through the metadata).\n25\t- `env.py` imports SQLAlchemy and the config module to get `DATABASE_URL`.\n26\t\n27\t**Schema evolution:**\n28\t- 0001 creates the initial schema (api_keys, events tables).\n29\t- 0002 extends the schema with the usage_rollup derived table and backfills it from events.\n30\t- Future migrations follow the same pattern: version number increments, only forward/backward are specified.\n31\t\n32\t## Notes\n33\t\n34\t**Migration strategy:**\n35\t- **Create migrations (0001):** initial schema. Reversible as \"schema + constraints\" (rows survive, schema is recreated).\n36\t- **Expand migrations (0002):** add a new table, backfill from existing data, then contract-ready for a future cutover (e.g., if we want to sunset the events table and go read-only on the rollup).\n37\t- Create migrations are always reversible (down = drop). Backfill migrations are reversible if the data can be re-derived (as in 0002, usage_rollup is derived from events, so recreating it is deterministic).\n38\t\n39\t**Reversibility (down paths):**\n40\t- 0001 down: drops events and api_keys (in FK-safe order: events first, then api_keys).\n41\t- 0002 down: drops usage_rollup (the table can be recreated by a future up run since the events data is intact).\n42\t\n43\t**Testing:**\n44\t- `tests/integration/test_migrations.py` runs the migration roundtrip (up → down → up) against a live test database.\n45\t- Verifies that schema is restored and constraints re-enforced (0001) and that backfilled data survives and is re-derived identically (0002).\n46\t- These tests are part of the acceptance criteria (AC10, AC11).\n47\t\n48\t**Deployment workflow:**\n49\t- Before deploying a new app version, the deployment pipeline runs `alembic upgrade head` on the target database.\n50\t- The app does not auto-migrate on startup; migrations are run explicitly (manual trigger or CI step).\n51\t- This gives operators control and ensures rollback-safety (if the app crashes after an upgrade, the migration is still committed, but the app can be rolled back to a prior version that understands the new schema).\n52\t\n53\t**Local development:**\n54\t- `alembic upgrade head` syncs your local database schema to the latest migration.\n55\t- `alembic downgrade -1` rolls back the last migration (useful for testing down paths).\n56\t- `alembic current` shows the current revision.\n57\t- `alembic history` shows all revisions.\n58\t"}]},"uuid":"5bcb6279-68d9-4525-8c1b-4cb6b02f7882","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:39:21.107Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"23171d46-d443-4791-bd62-685237bd998f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
