{"parentUuid":"8ece7d20-6d8a-440f-815b-e0c88dfdb183","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VhxNSDvpyHqcwLQBybKnxT","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# <Directory name>\n2\t\n3\t> Per-directory README template. Fill in; delete sections that don't apply.\n4\t> Update only affected sections on later changes — diff, don't rewrite.\n5\t\n6\t## Purpose\n7\t\n8\tOne or two sentences: what this directory is responsible for and why it exists.\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File / module | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `<file>` | <one line> |\n15\t\n16\t## Relationships\n17\t\n18\tHow the modules here relate to each other and to the rest of the system. Note\n19\tthe public surface (what other code imports) versus internals hidden behind it.\n20\tIf this directory is a facade (auth, logging, config), say so and name the\n21\tpublic entry points.\n22\t\n23\t## Notes (optional)\n24\t\n25\tNon-obvious constraints, env vars consumed, or gotchas a maintainer needs.\n26\t"}]},"uuid":"6ee26d37-3de6-470a-900c-7fa1cd48d98c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:40:09.323Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8ece7d20-6d8a-440f-815b-e0c88dfdb183","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
