{"parentUuid":"abd4cb9e-ca6f-41c6-adc8-f419f874cc17","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccqno5r7foFXWJ8nZBAxj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VyyPHJSHN4B1JiB18FsDfM","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\db\\README.md","old_string":"## Notes\n\n**Connection pooling:**","new_string":"## Notes\n\n**Isolation level (explicit pin):**\n- `get_engine()` pins `isolation_level=\"READ COMMITTED\"` on the async engine rather than\n  inheriting the DB/role default. `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`'s\n  `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` locks the `quotas` row (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`) then\n  reads `usage_rollup` as a **separate** statement; that second read only sees the prior\n  lock holder's committed increment because each statement gets a fresh snapshot under\n  READ COMMITTED. Under REPEATABLE READ a lock-waiter would read a stale rollup total and\n  admit events past the quota cap. Regression-guarded by `tests/test_db_session_isolation.py`.\n\n**Connection pooling:**"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":732,"cache_read_input_tokens":82747,"output_tokens":460,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":732},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":460,"cache_read_input_tokens":82747,"cache_creation_input_tokens":732,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":732,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqno4fRfo5B2WADf7dvx","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"c588d38c-45a6-4830-9ac2-0bac9c47bba3","