{"parentUuid":"c3497e02-84a2-4049-872c-274f22aa0239","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnqHF2YYkGwLSHjfPuv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update `scripts/README.md` for the `--admin` flag and the dast-review.sh/guard-source-markers.sh changes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":531,"cache_read_input_tokens":87444,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":531,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnqFqwa1gVrmRYeNCPw","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"5f120acb-8759-44de-9be4-40a1965b6d2e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:41:37.672Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"5f120acb-8759-44de-9be4-40a1965b6d2e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqnqHF2YYkGwLSHjfPuv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017XJQBxj7MQeQAuKJc7VCHx","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\scripts\\README.md","old_string":"| `seed_api_key.py` | Generates and provisions a new API key: creates a random secret, hashes it with Argon2id, inserts it into the database as a new `api_keys` row. Output includes the public key_id and the secret (displayed once, never stored). Used for initial key setup and test key generation. |\n| `smoke_import_check.py` | Python import smoke test: attempts to import the main app module (`src.main`) to catch syntax errors and early import failures before deployment. Run by the CI smoke-check hook. |\n| `ci/lockfile-check.sh` | Validates that `poetry.lock` is in sync with `pyproject.toml` (no stale/diverged dependencies). Run by CI before build. |\n| `ci/asvs-sast.sh` | ASVS Tier-1 SAST hook: runs Semgrep with project-specific rules to detect common security issues. Output feeds into the security report. |\n| `ci/dast-review.sh` | DAST review aggregator: collects and summarizes findings from runtime security scanning (e.g., OWASP ZAP). Run post-deployment. |\n| `ci/guard-source-markers.sh` | Validates that all deployment-critical markers are in place (e.g., PR description file, release notes). |","new_string":"| `seed_api_key.py` | Generates and provisions a new API key: creates a random secret, hashes it with Argon2id, inserts it into the database as a new `api_keys` row. `--admin` provisions `scope='admin'` (required to call `PUT /v1/quotas`); omitted, the key defaults to `scope='ingest'`. Output includes the public key_id and the secret (displayed once, never stored). Used for initial key setup and test key generation. |\n| `smoke_import_check.py` | Python import smoke test: attempts to import the main app module (`src.main`) to catch syntax errors and early import failures before deployment. Run by the CI smoke-check hook. |\n| `ci/lockfile-check.sh` | Validates that `poetry.lock` is in sync with `pyproject.toml` (no stale/diverged dependencies). Run by CI before build. |\n| `ci/asvs-sast.sh` | ASVS Tier-1 SAST hook: runs Semgrep with project-specific rules to detect common security issues. Output feeds into the security report. |\n| `ci/dast-review.sh` | DAST review aggregator: collects and summarizes findings from runtime security scanning (e.g., OWASP ZAP). Also reads the target-reachability probe (`.pipeline/dast-target-probe.json`) and surfaces a `target_reached: false` case as an advisory warning — a passive scan that never reached the real page would otherwise report a misleadingly clean \"within budget\" result. Run post-deployment. |\n| `ci/guard-source-markers.sh` | Greps the change set for experimental-revert / must-not-ship danger markers and blocks (exit 2) if found; used both as a hard deploy-gate check and as a mid-session self-check. Excludes `tests/`, `.pipeline/`, and its own definition file under both `global-hooks/` and `scripts/ci/` (the per-project scaffold copy) by exact filename, so a real marker anywhere else in `scripts/ci/` still blocks. |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":531,"cache_read_input_tokens":87444,"output_tokens":1288,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":531},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1288,"cache_read_input_tokens":87444,"cache_creation_input_tokens":531,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":531,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnqFqwa1gVrmRYeNCPw","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"bb314b6c-5bb0-404e-bbfb-7e380368cc29","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:41:47.166Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
