{"parentUuid":"835a8d12-9b9a-40a4-99f9-b3c0a40fed39","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccqnss3KdbSJ8FVgxVjZ6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0149iNYD5BPBfDUM8UNX4CmX","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd \"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\" && for f in tests/test_*.py; do echo \"== $f ==\"; sed -n '1,6p' \"$f\"; done","description":"Peek docstrings of top-level test files"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":418,"cache_read_input_tokens":91602,"output_tokens":321,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":418},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":91602,"cache_creation_input_tokens":418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":418,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqnsLYGdJBqp9o3pT9zm","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"8845d1f4-40f4-4cb1-8272-1355cbabe352","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:42:16.321Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"8845d1f4-40f4-4cb1-8272-1355cbabe352","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0149iNYD5BPBfDUM8UNX4CmX","type":"tool_result","content":"== tests/test_app_smoke.py ==\n\"\"\"App-construction-level tests that need no database or Redis connection:\nliveness, OpenAPI exposure (DAST-1), and the unauthenticated-denial/error-\nenvelope shape (AC18/AC19), all of which resolve before any DB/Redis call.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport pytest\n== tests/test_auth_api_key.py ==\n\"\"\"Tests for split-token parsing and the in-process verification cache\n(AC18 unauthenticated-denial cases; the Argon2id-vs-p95 cache mechanism).\"\"\"\n\nfrom src.auth import ApiKeyVerificationCache\nfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal, generate_split_token, parse_split_token\nfrom src.crypto import sha256_digest\n== tests/test_crypto.py ==\n\"\"\"Tests for the DataProtection crypto facade (AC8/AC-DATA-PROTECTION).\"\"\"\n\nfrom src.crypto import constant_time_equals, hash_secret, sha256_digest, verify_secret\n\n\ndef test_hash_secret_produces_an_argon2id_hash_not_plaintext():\n== tests/test_dast_context_documented.py ==\n\"\"\"AC24 (DAST-3): the scanner auth context — header name + token shape — must\nbe documented somewhere a DAST job (ZAP/Schemathesis config) can read it.\"\"\"\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n_REPO_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n== tests/test_db_session_isolation.py ==\n\"\"\"Regression guard for the quota lock-then-read isolation dependency (U-03).\n\n`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::read_tenant_quota_state_locked` takes a row\nlock on `quotas` (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`) and then reads\n`usage_rollup.total_quantity` in a SEPARATE plain statement. That second read\nonly observes the previous lock holder's committed rollup increment under\n== tests/test_dependency_pins.py ==\n\"\"\"Security-regression guard for the deploy-gating starlette CVE remediation.\n\n`starlette 0.41.3` carried four HIGH / CVSS-7.5 CVEs (GHSA-7f5h-v6xp-fcq8,\nGHSA-82w8-qh3p-5jfq, GHSA-wqp7-x3pw-xc5r, PYSEC-2026-249) plus six MODERATE/LOW.\nAll ten are cleared in starlette 1.3.1. The deployment gate blocks on\n`osv_max_cvss >= 7.0`, so a silent downgrade of starlette back into the\n== tests/test_logging_redaction.py ==\n\"\"\"AC9 (data_protection log-sink half): a raw `customer_id` (or any other\nsensitive field) must never reach the rendered log line, regardless of which\ncall site logs it.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\n\n== tests/test_rate_limit_fail_open.py ==\n\"\"\"Regression test for the Tier-2 rate-limit logging facade (AC14/AC16).\n\nGuards the missing `get_logger` import in `src/auth/rate_limit.py` that turned\nboth `get_logger` call sites in `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` into unhandled 500s\n(`NameError: name 'get_logger' is not defined`).\n\n== tests/test_schemas_events.py ==\n\"\"\"Validation-contract tests for `EventCreateRequest` (AC13).\"\"\"\n\nfrom decimal import Decimal\n\nimport pytest\nfrom hypothesis import given\n== tests/test_schemas_quotas.py ==\n\"\"\"Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (AC5, AC18).\"\"\"\n\nimport pytest\nfrom hypothesis import given\nfrom hypothesis import strategies as st\nfrom pydantic import ValidationError\n== tests/test_schemas_usage.py ==\n\"\"\"Validation-contract tests for `UsageQueryParams` (AC15).\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\n\nimport pytest\nfrom pydantic import ValidationError\n== tests/test_slo_alarms_defined.py ==\n\"\"\"AC12 (AC-SLO): SLOs (99.9% availability, ingest p95 < 50 ms) must be\ndefined as code via CloudWatch burn-rate + canary alarms, and the prod\nenvironment must resolve to the exact alarm names `deploy.yml`'s\n`<PROD_ALARM_NAMES>` expects.\n\nThis is a static assertion over the Terraform source (not a `terraform\n== tests/test_time_windows.py ==\n\"\"\"Tests for the UTC hour-flooring helper shared by both services.\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\n\nfrom hypothesis import given\nfrom hypothesis import strategies as st","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"9f80ff36-a65b-490a-ba1d-b7e88c158ef3","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:42:40.911Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8845d1f4-40f4-4cb1-8272-1355cbabe352","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"9f80ff36-a65b-490a-ba1d-b7e88c158ef3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"The coordinator sent a message while you were working:\nYou were resumed after a turn cap. Continue from where you stopped — you had updated the per-directory READMEs up to scripts/README.md (the --admin flag + the dast-review.sh/guard-source-markers.sh sync were next). Do not re-edit files you already updated. Still outstanding after scripts/README.md: any remaining touched-directory READMEs, then write .pipeline/pr-description.md and .pipeline/review-manifest.json (neither exists yet). Remember the PR description must surface: the human-revised AC20 (relative-to-baseline; 50 ms absolute moved to CI/staging load-campaign), the security FORCE-RLS fix + the pre-existing events/usage_rollup non-FORCE follow-up, the pytest CVE bump recommendation, the DAST L1 advisory result (within budget, 6 docs-page hygiene warnings), and the known single-key-per-tenant quota constraint (plan Open Q3).\n\nAddress this before completing your current task."},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"7ce52eb6-b13b-4fbb-a757-e01838a801b0","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:43:16.955Z","origin":{"kind":"coordinator"},"userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"7ce52eb6-b13b-4fbb-a757-e01838a801b0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<command-message>doc-conventions</command-message>\n<command-name>doc-conventions</command-name>\n<skill-format>true</skill-format>"},{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: C:\\Users\\brett\\.claude\\skills\\doc-conventions\n\n<!-- loading: PRELOAD by documentation — generated by scripts/list-skills.sh --annotate; do not hand-edit (source of truth: agent skills: frontmatter) -->\n\n# Documentation conventions\n\nYou keep docs current across every directory a change touches, then write the PR\ndescription and record the reviewed-state hash. Templates are siblings:\n`readme-template.md`, `pr-description-template.md`, `diagram-examples.md`.\n\n## Incremental-update rule (the core discipline)\n\n**Diff, don't rewrite.** Update only the directories and diagrams the change\nactually affects. For an existing file, change only the sections that moved;\nnever regenerate a whole README or the whole architecture file from scratch.\n\n## Per-directory README.md\n\nEvery directory touched by the change must have a README covering: the\ndirectory's **purpose**, the **modules** it contains, and how they **relate**.\nCreate if missing; otherwise update only affected sections. See\n`readme-template.md`.\n\n## Root README.md\n\nProject overview, setup, how to run locally, how to deploy, how to contribute.\nUpdate **only** if one of those steps changed.\n\n## system_architecture.md\n\nEnd-to-end narrative plus at least one Mermaid diagram tracing the full\nrequest/data flow. Update when the change affects **data flow, service\nboundaries, API contracts, or external integrations**. Regenerate only the\naffected diagrams.\n\nWhat belongs here vs a directory README: `system_architecture.md` is\n**cross-cutting** (how components fit together); a directory README is **local**\n(what this folder does).\n\n## Diagram types (Mermaid)\n\n| Purpose | Diagram |\n|---|---|\n| Request / data flow | `flowchart` (TD for hierarchy, LR for pipelines) |\n| Auth handshakes, sequenced calls | `sequenceDiagram` |\n| Data models / schema relationships | `erDiagram` |\n\nName nodes for what they are (`API`, `AuthProvider`, `OrdersDB`), not `A`/`B`.\nSee `diagram-examples.md`.\n\n## PR description\n\nWrite `.pipeline/pr-description.md`: summary of the change, link to the plan and\nthreat model in `.pipeline/plan.md`, notable decisions, and test/coverage\nhighlights. The deployment gate checks this file exists. See\n`pr-description-template.md`.\n\n## Design-record retention (`docs/decisions/`) — before the hash\n\n`.pipeline/` is per-feature and gitignored; the design record must outlive it. Copy,\nper feature branch, into the project:\n\n```\ndocs/decisions/<feature-branch>/\n├── plan.md            ← always\n├── acceptance.md      ← always\n├── plan-audit.md      ← always\n├── security-report.md ← always\n├── design-spec.md     ← when the run had a design source\n└── run-summary.json   ← when present (written at GREEN, before documentation)\n```\n\n- **Order matters:** copy *before* running `write-review-manifest.sh`, so the recorded\n  hash — and the human's diff approval — covers the record (`compute-change-hash.sh`\n  includes untracked files, so the new copies enter the change set automatically).\n- **Redaction:** the reports are secret-free by the security agent's rules; re-scan the\n  copies anyway — they are about to be committed.\n- **Not machine-gated:** evidence for humans, audits, and CI-era reviewers; no gate or\n  CI job reads it.\n- **Waivers that must survive into CI** live in **committed, tool-native ignore files**\n  (`osv-scanner.toml`, `.trivyignore`, `.semgrepignore`) — visible in the diff, so\n  human-reviewed at the diff checkpoint. A local-only `.pipeline/waivers.json` entry\n  that never lands in a committed ignore file will (correctly) fail the CI re-run —\n  the committed file IS the CI-side waiver record.\n\n## Record the reviewed-state hash — LAST\n\nAfter every README / `system_architecture.md` / source edit is written, record\nthe currency anchor (this must be your final action, so it captures the exact\nbytes the human reviews and deployment commits). Run the helper hook, which uses\nthe shared `compute-change-hash.sh` (the same hash the deployment gate recomputes,\nso they match byte-for-byte) and writes the manifest:\n\n```bash\n$HOME/.claude/hooks/write-review-manifest.sh\n# writes {\"reviewed_change_hash\":\"<sha256>\",\"ran_at\":\"<UTC ISO-8601>\"} to\n# .pipeline/review-manifest.json\n```\n\n`.pipeline/` is gitignored, so writing this file doesn't change the hash. The\nscript is covered by the `Bash($HOME/.claude/hooks/*.sh)` allow-list, so it runs\nwithout per-binary permission prompts.\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"b20f84c1-dd59-4cc9-ba95-ab19d8c9607e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:43:16.960Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
