{"parentUuid":"4be5a285-fc73-4856-8102-b62137481f50","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PjcefTTzhPA6Ak7Mozd7x8","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Meterly — system architecture\n2\t\n3\t## Overview\n4\t\n5\tMeterly ingests metered usage events, serves aggregated per-customer/metric\n6\tcounters, and enforces admin-set per-customer, per-metric usage caps\n7\t(\"quotas\"). Three authenticated HTTP endpoints, one PostgreSQL database, one\n8\tRedis rate-limit store, running as a Docker container on ECS Fargate behind an ALB.\n9\t\n10\t```\n11\tClient --HTTPS+API key--> ALB --> FastAPI (ECS Fargate, >=2 tasks)\n12\t                                     |-- Tier-1 (IP) / Tier-2 (api_key_id) throttle --> Redis\n13\t                                     |-- bound-parameter SQL, RLS-scoped -------------> RDS PostgreSQL\n14\t                                     |-- DB credential fetch ------------------------> Secrets Manager\n15\t                                     |-- traces/logs/errors -------------------------> CloudWatch/X-Ray/Sentry\n16\t```\n17\t\n18\t## Request flow — `POST /v1/events`\n19\t\n20\t1. Request-id/trace assigned, security headers queued (`src/logging/middleware.py`, `src/api/middleware.py`)."}]},"uuid":"62c442ac-f2b2-4950-94c4-9c2203ffc6c5","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:44:58.218Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4be5a285-fc73-4856-8102-b62137481f50","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
