{"parentUuid":"35e6189a-0544-48fd-9432-d40eb10a9258","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KacM9NYdK6ZDn5g2LZRgkV","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Meterly\n2\t\n3\tUsage-metering ingestion API. See `PROJECT.md` for the product spec and\n4\t`docs/system_architecture.md` for the implementation overview.\n5\t\n6\t## Quickstart\n7\t\n8\t```bash\n9\tpoetry install\n10\tpoetry run alembic upgrade head\n11\tpoetry run uvicorn src.main:app --port 8000\n12\t```\n13\t\n14\t`GET /health` returns 200 with no dependencies (liveness). `GET /health/ready`\n15\tchecks the database connection and migration head (readiness).\n16\t"}]},"uuid":"8c441e48-646d-4b16-8e1f-838960329de1","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:45:16.189Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"35e6189a-0544-48fd-9432-d40eb10a9258","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
