{"parentUuid":"eee342a3-d593-4532-bd0e-d60a2e0c6bdf","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XVGAX15VkA9ARuiFf1javd","type":"tool_result","content":"399:## Open questions\n400-\n401-1. **PUT /v1/quotas latency budget** (the brief's single Open item). The stated p95 < 50 ms budget is\n402-   for `POST /v1/events` only. *Proposed default:* **p95 < 100 ms** for `PUT /v1/quotas` as a\n403-   documented target, **not** a load-tested AC — it is an admin-only, low-traffic route doing a single\n404-   indexed upsert, so a sustained k6 load test would be over-engineering. Confirm at the checkpoint,\n405-   or raise the budget to a hard AC if admin tooling is expected to batch-set quotas at volume.\n--\n469:  this slice (Open Question 3); quotas bind to a single `api_key_id`.\n470-\n471-### Threat-model diagram (Mermaid DFD)\n472-\n473-```mermaid\n474-flowchart TD\n475-    admin[Admin/Ingest API client]:::ext","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"4bc5c224-1606-496d-b0ae-362611f5ba56","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:51:11.159Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"eee342a3-d593-4532-bd0e-d60a2e0c6bdf","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
