{"parentUuid":"7ee049a2-2026-40c9-8e87-3eb2d0aa81fd","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a594aec0f6deff72c","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccqoh8W4Mqwdv61TRbmhs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Documentation pass complete. Summary of what was updated for the `feature/metric-quotas` change (gates confirmed clean: security-report.md `status: clean`, test-results.json `status: pass`):\n\n**Per-directory READMEs**\n- Updated (already largely current in the working tree from a prior step; I verified accuracy against source and closed remaining gaps): `c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\README.md`, `src\\auth\\README.md`, `src\\repositories\\README.md`, `src\\services\\README.md`\n- Newly updated by me: `src\\db\\README.md` (added the `isolation_level=\"READ COMMITTED\"` pin rationale), `alembic\\README.md` (added migration `0003` to Modules/Schema evolution/Reversibility), `scripts\\README.md` (added `seed_api_key.py --admin` flag, corrected a stale/invented `--key_id` CLI-arg claim after verifying the real argparse definition, documented `dast-review.sh`'s target-reachability probe and `guard-source-markers.sh`'s exclusion fix)\n- Newly created: `tests\\README.md`, `tests\\integration\\README.md`, `tests\\integration\\k6\\README.md`\n\n**system_architecture.md** (`docs\\system_architecture.md`): added a Mermaid `flowchart` request/data-flow diagram (the file previously had only an ASCII diagram, no Mermaid — now compliant); prose sections for `PUT /v1/quotas`, the `quotas` data model, and the quota lock-then-read atomicity were already present and verified accurate against source.\n\n**Root docs**: `README.md` unchanged (setup/run/deploy steps didn't change). `CLAUDE.md`/`PROJECT.md` already updated in the working tree for the `scope` model.\n\n**Design-record retention**: copied `plan.md`, `acceptance.md`, `plan-audit.md`, `security-report.md`, `run-summary.json` into `docs\\decisions\\feature\\metric-quotas\\` (no `design-spec.md` — this run had no design source); scanned copies for credential-shaped content, found none beyond an already-triaged test-only literal.\n\n**PR description**: written to `.pipeline\\pr-description.md` — surfaces the 21 test-covered + 1 delegated-to-security composition (AC22), branch coverage (58.3%) and the advisory test-quality signal, a Supply chain section (lockfile clean, SBOM 65 components), the DAST advisory section (target reached, within budget, 6 docs-page hygiene alert types), the human-revised AC20 relative bound, the RLS `FORCE` fix plus the pre-existing `events`/`usage_rollup` follow-up, the `pytest` CVE bump recommendation, and the single-admin-key-per-tenant accepted constraint.\n\n**Reviewed-state hash**: `.pipeline\\review-manifest.json` written last via `write-review-manifest.sh` (`reviewed_change_hash=63cc71073119d344c72b61899df9c1ca8259b9787b92bf2a5903b8e3b904fd38`).\n\nOne judgment call worth flagging to the user: I did not create a `.github/README.md` — no prior feature in this repo created one for the CI-workflow directory, and it doesn't fit the module-facade README convention, so I treated it as out of scope like the preceding two shipped features did."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":182,"cache_read_input_tokens":127336,"output_tokens":1150,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":182},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1150,"cache_read_input_tokens":127336,"cache_creation_input_tokens":182,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":182,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqoh7BSWoUy1DdJJs6F7","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant